<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-13T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-13T19:00:00-05:00" n="766" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d766">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">125.6336/12–948: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Smith</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-13T19:00:00-05:00">December 13,
                                1948—7 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1388. In your discretion pls use subject matter Dairen’s 97, Dec 9,<note n="66" xml:id="d766fn66">Sent to the Department as telegram No. 230,
                                <ref target="#pg_844">p. 844</ref>.</note> as basis for request Sov
                        FonOff for according of such facilities as would give us such a temporary
                        means of communication with ConGen Mukden.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>